stratificationFactors: Extent of psoriasis (>= 3% BSA or < 3% BSA)
Current use of at least 1 DMARD
Number of prior failed biologic DMARDs (1 vs > 1)

arms.name: Group 1: upadacitinib 15 mg QD
arms.description: Subjects receive upadacitinib 15 mg once daily for the duration of the study.

arms.name: Group 2: upadacitinib 30 mg QD
arms.description: Subjects receive upadacitinib 30 mg once daily. Note: Per Amendment 8, subjects on 30mg will be switched to 15mg at their next visit.

arms.name: Group 3: Placebo followed by upadacitinib 15 mg QD
arms.description: Subjects receive placebo for the first 24 weeks, then switch to upadacitinib 15 mg once daily.

arms.name: Group 4: Placebo followed by upadacitinib 30 mg QD
arms.description: Subjects receive placebo for the first 24 weeks, then switch to upadacitinib 30 mg once daily.

cohorts.name: Bio-IR
cohorts.characteristic: Subjects with moderately to severely active Psoriatic Arthritis who have an inadequate response to at least one biologic DMARD

epochs.name: Period 1 (Weeks 24-56)
epochs.description: Blinded treatment where placebo subjects switch to active upadacitinib

epochs.name: Period 2
epochs.description: Long-term extension (up to 3 years total) initially blinded then open-label
